parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Seat Belt Design for Tall Individuals
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The current seat belt design can cause throat injuries and potentially fatal strangulation for individuals over six feet tall, especially during minor accidents or hard braking.
symptoms: Seat belt rubs against the neck
shoulder belt wraps around the neck
difficulty wearing the seat belt comfortably
and increased risk of injury or death.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belt does not retract properly
seat belt fails to lock in place
and seat belt binds or won't retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to come undone during an accident, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: seat belt fails to lock in place
and seat belt comes undone during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to restrain occupants properly can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belt fails to hold occupants secure
seat belt does not lock in position
and occupants are not properly restrained during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator belt can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potential accidents.
symptoms: The alternator belt keeps popping off

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the MAP sensor can cause stalling, poor performance, and deacceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or seize, leading to a loss of power and potential accidents.
Water pump failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage and potential failure.
Fuel system malfunction can cause the vehicle to deaccelerate, leading to a loss of power and potential accidents.
Engine noise and vibration can indicate underlying engine problems, which can lead to engine failure and potential accidents.
symptoms: noisy engine due to loose fan belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Manifold compression sensor failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potential accidents.
symptoms: Stalling due to manifold compression sensor failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle fires can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
symptoms: Vehicle caught on fire in the engine compartment without prior warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake rotors can cause the brakes to pulsate or vibrate, leading to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and potentially accidents.
The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of braking power, increased stopping distances, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: brakes do not activate on time

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the brakes to pulsate or vibrate, leading to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and potentially accidents.
